<br>
You know, in general I try to be very helpful to others.  If I'm sittin on my druid ass in a zone, doing nothing.. and see someone shouting for a port, I almost always give them a lift.  <br>
<br>
I do not EVER accept donations, unless someone tricks me with a split before they disband the group.  I figure, I play my monk.. and I know how frustrating it can be to be stuck somewhere, without sow.. and think of the long, boring run ahead. <br>
<br>
Maybe having said that, this shouldn't bother me but.. it does.<br>
<br>
The other day, I'm sitting in WC and some poor sap is ooc'ing for a port and saying he'll donate 100pp.  Now, I'm with a group.. and we're just waiting on someone, but I can't stand to think that someone is going to take advantage of this guy... port him, and take his 100pp for something so easy.  <br>
<br>
So, I tell me group &quot;Guys, I'm gonna go port this guy really fast so he doesn't have to waste his money&quot;  they say ok, I tell the guy I'll take him.<br>
<br>
I port him to GD... and the second we zone in, he immediately takes off running, disbands.. and doesn't even say thank you.  Now, I of course wouldn't have accepted any pp he tried to give me... but just the fact that he didn't even try, much less thank me for the favor. <br>
<br>
At the VERY least, say thank you before you take off running.  Is that asking so much?  And you then wonder why people stop helping each other just for the sake of being kind?  <br>
<br>
The thing about this game.. is that you can be as big of an asshole as you want, because nobody can really touch you.  You have something to hide behind... sort of like how people are bigger assholes while they're driving than they would be to your face.  It's easy to be a jerk when you have no fear of being confronted for it.   <p>Manae Bananae
<br>53 Druid 
